headline.main: LATEST INTELLIGENCE; State Department-Gen. Case-No Probability of the Speedy Admission of Kansas as a State-Difficulties with New-Granada-Dallas Clarendon Treaty-Our Relations with Mexico-Lower California and Sonora to be Annexed. By Telegraph to the New-York Daily Times. Magnetic Telegraph Co.'s Offices-4 Hanover-st., and 181 Broadway. INTERESTING FROM WASHINGTON.

headline.main: IMPORTANT FROM NEW-GRANADA.; Probable Suspension of Diplomatic Relations between the two Countries. Rejection of the Demands of the United States by the Government.

docs.lead_paragraph: We have received newspaper dates from Begeta to the 17th February, and my private letters are to the 20th. The news is important, and such as you have anticipated, no doubt, from the tenor of my correspondence in regard to the decision of the question between the United States and New-Granada.
